org.apache.flex.abc.semantics

Class Name

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.abc.semantics.Name

  • public class Name
extends Object
    A representation of a name.

    All names are stored as multinames in the ABC, but this view of a name differentiates regular multinames, runtime multinames, and type names.

      • Name

        public Name(Name typename_base,
    Name typename_parameter)
        Construct a Name of kind CONSTANT_TypeName, which represents a parameterized type such as C.<T>. getBaseName() and getQualifiers() will return null, but getTypeNameBase() returns the Name for type C, and getTypeNameParameter() returns the Name for type T.
        Parameters:
        typename_base - The Name for type C.
        typename_parameter - The Name for type T.

      • initTypeName

        public void initTypeName(Name base,
                Name parameter)
        Method to init a type name with a base name and parameter name. This method is to facilitate reading in a Name table from an ABC - the type name may refer to names which have not been read yet, so the values cannot be filled in until later. This will assert if this name is not a type name, or if it has already been initialized with values that are different than those passed in.
        Parameters:
        base - the base name this type name should use
        parameter - the parameter name this type name should use
